# Release signing — copy this file to `key.properties` (same directory)
# and fill in the real values. BOTH files are gitignored.
#
# Setup (run once, on a secure machine, never commit the output):
#   1. Generate the upload keystore:
#        keytool -genkey -v -keystore android/app/upload-keystore.jks \
#          -keyalg RSA -keysize 2048 -validity 10000 -alias upload
#      You'll be prompted for a store password AND a key password
#      (they can be the same, but it's better practice to use different
#      values). Remember BOTH — if you lose them you can never update
#      the app on Google Play.
#
#   2. Copy this file and fill in the values:
#        cp android/key.properties.example android/key.properties
#        $EDITOR android/key.properties
#
#   3. Verify Gradle picks it up:
#        ./gradlew :app:signingReport
#      Look for the "release" variant and confirm the SHA-256 fingerprint
#      matches `keytool -list -v -keystore android/app/upload-keystore.jks`.
#      That fingerprint is what you paste into
#      android/app/src/main/res/values/assetlinks.json for App Links.
#
#   4. Build a signed release APK:
#        flutter build apk --release
#
#   5. Store a backup of upload-keystore.jks + the passwords in a
#      password manager (1Password / Bitwarden "API keys" vault) and
#      in your CI provider's secret store. Lost keystore = locked out
#      of Google Play for the lifetime of the app.
#
# ─── File format ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# keyAlias       — the `-alias` flag you passed to keytool (default: upload)
# keyPassword    — the password for the key (set during keytool's prompts)
# storeFile      — relative path from android/ to the .jks file
# storePassword  — the password for the keystore (set during keytool's prompts)
#
# Example values (REPLACE before saving):
#
# keyAlias=upload
# keyPassword=CHANGEME_key_password_here
# storeFile=app/upload-keystore.jks
# storePassword=CHANGEME_store_password_here

keyAlias=upload
keyPassword=replace_me
storeFile=app/upload-keystore.jks
storePassword=replace_me
